Win32ErrorCode Enumeration
Specifies system error codes for the Windows API functions.

These error codes are returned by the GetLastWin32Error function when a function fails.

Namespace:  DevCase.Win32.Enums
Assembly:  DevCase (in DevCase.dll) Version: 4.0.0.0 (4.0)

ERROR_STATE_CREATE_CONTAINER_FAILED15805 State Manager failed to create the container.
ERROR_STATE_DELETE_CONTAINER_FAILED15806 State Manager failed to delete the container.

ERROR_STATE_WRITE_SETTING_FAILED15808 State Manager failed to write the setting.
ERROR_STATE_DELETE_SETTING_FAILED15809 State Manager failed to delete the setting.
ERROR_STATE_QUERY_SETTING_FAILED15810 State Manager failed to query the setting.
ERROR_STATE_READ_COMPOSITE_SETTING_FAILED15811 State Manager failed to read the composite setting.
ERROR_STATE_WRITE_COMPOSITE_SETTING_FAILED15812 State Manager failed to write the composite setting.
ERROR_STATE_ENUMERATE_CONTAINER_FAILED15813 State Manager failed to enumerate the containers.
ERROR_STATE_ENUMERATE_SETTINGS_FAILED15814 State Manager failed to enumerate the settings.

ERROR_STATE_SETTING_VALUE_SIZE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED15816 The size of the state manager setting value has exceeded the limit.
ERROR_STATE_SETTING_NAME_SIZE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED15817 The length of the state manager setting name has exceeded the limit.
